  "response": "# Verdict: REJECT\n\n## Overall Assessment\n\nThis component has **critical accessibility violations** that block deaf/hard of hearing users from accessing content entirely. The missing caption track element is a fundamental failure per WCAG 1.2.2, and the generic aria-label \"Video player\" provides no meaningful information to screen reader users about actual video content. This design must be rejected before implementation proceeds\u2014these are not minor issues but blocking accessibility failures.\n\n## Pre-commitment Predictions\n\n| Prediction | Actual Finding |\n|------------|-----------------|\n| Missing track element for captions | \u2713 Confirmed - CRITICAL gap |\n| Generic aria-label on video | \u2713 Confirmed - MAJOR issue |\n| No caption toggle button exists | \u2713 Confirmed - CRITICAL feature missing |\n| Keyboard controls accessible | Partially true (play/pause works, but no caption control) |\n\n## Critical Findings\n\n### 1. Missing Caption Track Element Blocks Deaf/Hard of Hearing Access\n\n**File:** `src/components/VideoPlayer.tsx:20-23`  \n```jsx\n<video\n  ref={videoRef}\n  src={videoSrc}\n  aria-label=\"Video player\"\n/>\n```\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **WCAG/APG** | WCAG 1.2.2 (Captions) \u2014 Media with audio must have synchronized captions available; WAI-ARIA Media Pattern requires `<track>` elements for closed captions/subtitles |\n| **User Group Impacted** | Deaf, hard of hearing users who rely on visual text to understand spoken content |\n| **Actual Behavior** | No track element exists in DOM. Captions data (`captions` prop) is available but cannot be rendered without `<track>` elements and a caption toggle button |\n| **Expected Behavior** | Video should have at least one `<track kind=\"subtitles\" srclang=\"en\">` element with `label`, `default` (if enabled by default), or controlled via UI; captions must be toggable per WCAG 1.2.4, 3.1.5 |\n| **Fix** | Add track elements: `<track kind=\"captions\" label=\"English Captions\" srclang=\"en\" src={captions} />`. Implement caption toggle button with `aria-label` and state management to enable/disable tracks via the video element's API or custom controls that manipulate them. |\n| **Confidence** | HIGH (direct code inspection) |\n\n### 2. Generic aria-label Provides No Meaningful Information\n\n**File:** `src/components/VideoPlayer.tsx:19-23`  \n```jsx\naria-label=\"Video player\"\n```\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **WCAG/APG** | WCAG 4.1.2 (Name, Role, Value) \u2014 Accessible name must describe the content/function; WAI-ARIA Media Pattern requires descriptive video labels or captions for context |\n| **User Group Impacted** | Screen reader users who need to understand what they're watching without seeing it visually |\n| **Actual Behavior** | \"Video player\" is generic and provides zero information about actual video content (e.g., product demo, tutorial, interview) |\n| **Expected Behavior** | aria-label should describe the specific content: `aria-label=\"Product demonstration of X features\"` or use a more descriptive accessible name that conveys context. For autoplaying videos with audio, captions are mandatory; for silent videos, visual descriptions may suffice but still need meaningful labels |\n| **Fix** | Replace generic label with dynamic description based on video metadata/content: `aria-label={videoTitle || 'Video content'}` or use `<figcaption>` outside the video element to provide context. Consider adding a title attribute as fallback (though aria-label takes precedence). |\n| **Confidence** | HIGH |\n\n### 3. Caption Toggle Button Missing Entirely\n\n**File:** `src/components/VideoPlayer.tsx:24-31`  \n```jsx\n<div className=\"controls\">\n  <button onClick={togglePlay} aria-label=\"Play or pause\">...</button>\n  {/* BUG: No caption toggle button visible or accessible */}\n</div>\n```\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **WCAG/APG** | WCAG 1.2.4 (Captions + Audio Descriptions) \u2014 Captions must be available and toggable; WAI-ARIA Media Pattern requires caption controls for user control over media features |\n| **User Group Impacted** | Deaf/hard of hearing users who need to enable captions, plus all users in noisy environments or with audio impairments |\n| **Actual Behavior** | No button exists. The `captions` prop is available but there's no UI element to toggle them on/off. This renders the caption feature unusable even if track elements were added later |\n| **Expected Behavior** | Caption toggle should be a `<button>` with clear label (e.g., \"CC\" icon + text), state indicated via `aria-pressed` or visible indicator, and keyboard accessible (Tab/Enter). When toggled, it should enable/disable the corresponding track element. Per WAI-ARIA Media Pattern, caption controls must have proper association to their target functionality |\n| **Fix** | Add button: `<button onClick={toggleCaptions} aria-label=\"Toggle captions\" className={`caption-toggle ${isCaptionsEnabled ? 'active' : ''}`} disabled={!captions}>CC</button>`. Implement state management for `isCaptionsEnabled` and sync with track element",
